==Sanskrit==
===Noun===
'''भगवान्'''

#[[Bhagavan]] - also written Bhagawan or Bhagwan (भगवान् in devanagari script, Bhagavān in IAST) is a Sanskrit word meaning Holy or Blessed one. Historically, it has been used by many spiritual masters in India including Gautama Buddha and other bodhisattvas, Ramana Maharshi and Rajneesh.